### Openvpn quick client change for asus-wrt ###
- Using openbot ssh client post login automation
- Written to remove need to login via GUI and constantly change VPN client for devices

HOW TO USE:
- enable ssh on asus-wrt (suggested different port and local access only)
- ssh to router and dump current vpn director file
- # cat /jffs/openvpn/vpndirector_rulelist
- Replace below one-liner with your vpndirector file.
- Paste whole one-liner into connectbot post login automation box. (note, the exit command is optional) 
- to change vpn client, simply modify the post automation one-liner accordingly for which VPN you want to use for each location. Save and connect. 

EXAMPLE:
# cat /jffs/openvpn/vpndirector_rulelist

<1>WORK>192.168.50.160>>WAN<1>PIXEL3>192.168.50.125>>OVPN2<1>BED>192.168.50.139>>OVPN2<1>PIXEL5>192.168.50.6>>OVPN3<1>LR>192.168.50.141>>OVPN4<1>ONN>192.168.50.115>>OVPN4<1>DELL>192.168.50.243>>OVPN5


EXAMPLE FULL ONELINER PASTED INTO CONNECTBOT: (first echo is just a fast glance of my vpn clients and locations. you do not need this)

echo "VPN1 - Lon \n VPN2 - Ten \n VPN3 - US \n VPN4 - Gsc \n VPN5 -  Ga \n"

echo "<1>WORK>192.168.50.160>>WAN<1>PIXEL3>192.168.50.125>>OVPN2<1>BED>192.168.50.139>>OVPN2<1>PIXEL5>192.168.50.6>>OVPN3<1>LR>192.168.50.141>>OVPN4<1>ONN>192.168.50.115>>OVPN4<1>DELL>192.168.50.243>>OVPN5" > /jffs/openvpn/vpndirector_rulelist && service restart_vpnrouting && exit
